Subtask 3.2: Conditional Statements
Basic If-Else Statements
Create a simple condition script:
$number = 15

if ($number -gt 10) {
    Write-Host "$number is greater than 10"
} else {
    Write-Host "$number is not greater than 10"
}
Multiple conditions with elseif:
$score = 85

if ($score -ge 90) {
    Write-Host "Grade: A"
} elseif ($score -ge 80) {
    Write-Host "Grade: B"
} elseif ($score -ge 70) {
    Write-Host "Grade: C"
} else {
    Write-Host "Grade: F"
}
Switch Statements
Create a switch statement example:
$day = "Monday"

switch ($day) {
    "Monday" { Write-Host "Start of the work week!" }
    "Friday" { Write-Host "TGIF!" }
    "Saturday" { Write-Host "Weekend time!" }
    "Sunday" { Write-Host "Rest day!" }
    default { Write-Host "Regular day" }
}
Subtask 3.3: Loops and Iteration
For Loops
Basic for loop:
