Troubleshooting Tips
Common Issues and Solutions
Issue 1: PowerShell Command Not Found
Problem: pwsh: command not found

Solution:

# Install PowerShell Core on Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y powershell
Issue 2: Permission Denied Errors
Problem: Cannot create files or directories

Solution:

# Check current permissions
Get-Location
# Ensure you're in a writable directory like your home folder
Set-Location ~
Issue 3: Script Execution Policy
Problem: Scripts won't run due to execution policy

Solution:

# Check current execution policy
Get-ExecutionPolicy
# Set execution policy for current user
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
Issue 4: Path Not Found Errors
Problem: Cannot find specified path

Solution:

# Always verify paths exist before operations
Test-Path "your/path/here"
# Use absolute paths when in doubt
$fullPath = Resolve-Path "relative/path"
